value.0: There are some dire wolves in the mountains there that have taken to preying on my herd. The pack's led by a big she-wolf I've taken to calling Silverback...
I swear I'll pay you a handsome amount of gold to have her head. She's already taken down two of my cattle and, left to her own devices, she'll clear the whole herd.
Well I'll warn you now, they aren't your everyday timber wolves. Dire wolves are a lot tougher and a lot more cunning. Smarter than my boy at any rate...
Perhaps so but I'm not a wealthy lady. There's not much money in cattle these days, and less when you're losing your herd to wolves...
They den in a cave somewhere to the north, though I know not where exactly. There are always a couple of them pacing in front.
Me? I'm Farmer O'Deel but you can just call me Mary, if you like. An' who might you be?
Thank you for all the help. Me and my cattle can rest easy, now...
